 According to the Restatement, (1) HN2[
] A promise to refrain from competition that imposes a restraint that is ancillary to an otherwise valid transaction 
or relationship is unreasonably in restraint of trade if (a) the restraint is greater than is needed to protect the promisee's legitimate interest, or (b) the promisee's need is outweighed by the hardship to the promisor and the likely injury to the public. RESTATEMENT (SECOND) OF CONTRACTS ยง 188 (1) (1979)

